lex h-auto w-full max-w-lg items-center justify-center overflow-hidden"><button type="button" aria-haspopup="dialog" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="radix-_r_ra_" data-state="closed" class="overflow-hidden rounded-[1.75rem] w-full h-full max-w-96 max-h-64" aria-label="Open image: Screenshot 2026-07-01 at 1.02.19 PM.png"><img alt="Screenshot 2026-07-01 at 1.02.19 PM.png" width="2048" height="1280" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="max-w-full object-cover object-center overflow-hidden rounded-[1.75rem] w-full h-full max-w-96 max-h-64 w-fit transition-opacity duration-300 opacity-0" src="./5.png_files/content(1)"></button></div></div></div></div><div class="flex flex-col w-fit max-w-(--user-chat-width,70%) items-start self-end rtl:items-end rtl:self-start"><div class="user-message-bubble-color corner-superellipse/0.98 relative min-w-0 overflow-hidden rounded-[22px] px-4 py-2.5 leading-6 rounded-se-lg w-full"><div data-custom-highlighting-behavior="boundary" class="A_HxFq_root" data-collapsed="" data-testid="collapsible-user-message-root" data-can-expand=""><div id="_r_mm_" data-testid="collapsible-user-message-content" class="A_HxFq_content"><div class="max-w-full min-w-0 [overflow-wrap:anywhere] whitespace-pre-wrap">im trying to do these Step 4: Upload your project from Terminal

After creating the repo, GitHub will show you a link like:

https://github.com/your-username/my-app.git

Now in Terminal, type these one by one:

git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial React app"
git branch -M main

Now connect your project to GitHub. Replace the link with your own repo link:

git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/my-app.git

Then push:

git push -u origin main

GitHub supports uploading existing local code to a GitHub repository using the command line.

Step 5: Share it with your manager

Since you want your manager to see everything, keep the repo Private and invite them.

On GitHub:

Your repo → Settings → Collaborators → Add people

Search your manager’s GitHub username or email, then send the invite. GitHub allows adding collaborators to private and public repos.

After they accept, they can see the code.

Important: don’t worry about node_modules; it should not upload because Vite projects usually include .gitignore.

